      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide3-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "What is Research?" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide3-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Research = Re + Search", "bold": true }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide3-list1",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s3-1", "content": [{ "text": "Re: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Again, a new, over again" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s3-2", "content": [{ "text": "Search: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "To examine closely and carefully, to test and try or to probe" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide3-img",
        "type": "image",
        "src": "/data/research-methods-se/rmse-chap1-intro-research-basics/images/slide3_magnifying_glass.png",
        "alt": "Stylized human figure holding a large magnifying glass over a blue question mark, illustrating the concept of search and inquiry in research.",
        "caption": [{ "text": "Visual representation of 'Search' in research." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide4-h3",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Definitions of Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide4-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "\"A careful inquiry specially through search for new facts in any branch of knowledge\" ", "italic": true },
          { "text": "(Oxford Dictionary)" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide4-p2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "\"Research comprises defining and redefining problems, formulating hypothesis or suggested solution; collecting, organizing and evaluating data; making deductions and reaching conclusion; and at last carefully testing the conclusions to determine whether they fit the formulating hypothesis.\" ", "italic": true },
          { "text": "(Clifford Woody)" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide4-img",
        "type": "image",
        "src": "/data/research-methods-se/rmse-chap1-intro-research-basics/images/slide4_research_newspaper.png",
        "alt": "Magnifying glass over a newspaper headline that says 'Research', symbolizing the investigation of facts.",
        "caption": [{ "text": "Research as an investigative process." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide5-h3",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Further Perspectives on Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide5-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "Research is a ", "bold": true }, { "text": "systematic process of inquiry", "bold": true },
          { "text": " to discover, interpret, or revise facts, theories, or applications (Walliman, 2011)." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide5-p2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "The basic nature of research is to ", "bold": true }, { "text": "advance knowledge and seek solutions to problems.", "bold": true }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide5-p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "In software engineering (SE), research addresses problems like improving code quality, optimizing algorithms, or enhancing user experience." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide6-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Why Study Research?" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide6-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s6-1", "content": [{ "text": "To Explore: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Investigate unknown phenomena or areas of interest." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s6-2", "content": [{ "text": "To Describe: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Provide detailed accounts of specific situations or populations." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s6-3", "content": [{ "text": "To Explain: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Understand relationships between variables and causation." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s6-4", "content": [{ "text": "To Predict: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Forecast future occurrences based on data analysis." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s6-5", "content": [{ "text": "To Influence: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Inform decisions and policy-making through evidence-based findings." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide7-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "What is NOT Research?" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide7-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s7-1", "content": [{ "text": "Gathering information from resources such as books or magazines is not a research." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s7-2", "content": [{ "text": "Merely transporting facts from one source to another doesn't constitute a research." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s7-3", "content": [{ "text": "Research is not simply learning about something." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s7-4", "content": [{ "text": "Research problems do not simply result in “Yes” or a “No” answer." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide8-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Goal of the Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide8-list1",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": true,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-1", "content": [{ "text": "To get a degree" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-2", "content": [{ "text": "To get respectability" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-3", "content": [{ "text": "To face a challenge" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-4", "content": [{ "text": "To solve a problem" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-5", "content": [{ "text": "To get intellectual joy" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-6", "content": [{ "text": "To serve society" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide8-list2",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-7", "content": [{ "text": "by increasing standard of living in case of Science and Tech. and" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s8-8", "content": [{ "text": "by showing right path to society in case of Social and Behavioural Sciences" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide9-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Nature of Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide9-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-1", "content": [{ "text": "Originate with a question or problem" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-2", "content": [{ "text": "Requires a clear articulation of a goal or objective" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-3", "content": [{ "text": "Requires a specific plan or procedure" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-4", "content": [{ "text": "Often divide main problem into sub-problems" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-5", "content": [{ "text": "Guided by specific problem, question, proposition or hypothesis" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-6", "content": [{ "text": "Accepts certain critical assumptions" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-7", "content": [{ "text": "Requires collection and interpretation of data" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s9-8", "content": [{ "text": "Cyclical (Helical) in nature" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide9-img",
        "type": "image",
        "src": "/data/research-methods-se/rmse-chap1-intro-research-basics/images/slide9_research_wordcloud.png",
        "alt": "A person writing on a transparent board with a word cloud related to research terms like 'statistic', 'data', 'result', 'report', 'project', 'survey', 'review', 'analysis', 'method', 'solution', 'explore', 'examine', 'development', 'fact'.",
        "caption": [{ "text": "Key aspects of the nature of research." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide10-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Qualities of Research - Features" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide10-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s10-1", "content": [{ "text": "Systematic ", "bold": true }, { "text": "– ordered structure of inquiry" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s10-2", "content": [{ "text": "Logical ", "bold": true }, { "text": "– process to evaluate conclusions drawn" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s10-3", "content": [{ "text": "Empirical ", "bold": true }, { "text": "– collection of data (facts, experience, etc.) on which to base decisions" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s10-4", "content": [{ "text": "Reductive ", "bold": true }, { "text": "– individual events (data) are used to establish general relationships" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s10-5", "content": [{ "text": "Replicable ", "bold": true }, { "text": "– process is recorded so findings and procedures can be tested again" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide10-img",
        "type": "image",
        "src": "/data/research-methods-se/rmse-chap1-intro-research-basics/images/slide10_research_wordcloud.png",
        "alt": "A person writing on a transparent board with a word cloud related to research terms (same as slide 9 image).",
        "caption": [{ "text": "Qualities defining robust research." }]
      },
       {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide11-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "The Research Process" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide11-h3",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Stages of the research:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide11-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": true,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-1", "content": [{ "text": "Identifying the Research Problem: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Formulating questions based on gaps in knowledge." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-2", "content": [{ "text": "Literature Review: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Reviewing existing studies to understand the context and background." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-3", "content": [{ "text": "Formulating Hypotheses: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Developing testable predictions based on theoretical frameworks." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-4", "content": [{ "text": "Research Design: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Planning how to conduct the research, including methodology and tools." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-5", "content": [{ "text": "Data Collection: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Gathering data through surveys, experiments, interviews, etc." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-6", "content": [{ "text": "Data Analysis: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Interpreting the data using statistical or qualitative methods." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-7", "content": [{ "text": "Drawing Conclusions: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Summarizing findings and determining their implications." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s11-8", "content": [{ "text": "Reporting and Dissemination: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Sharing results through publications, presentations, or reports." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
