      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide15-citation",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
            { "text": "Citation: ", "bold": true },
            { "text": "Cooper & Schindler (2009): \"Design determines the validity and reliability of findings.\"", "italic": true }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide16-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Theory" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide16-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Dubin (1978) notes theory contains three main elements:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide16-list1",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-1", "content": [{ "text": "A set of well-defined concepts (or units);" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-2", "content": [{ "text": "Laws of interaction: rules governing (or interrelationships between the units/concepts);" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-3", "content": [{ "text": "Boundary: Scope where the theory applies." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide16-h3-ex",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Example:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide16-list2",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-4", "content": [{ "text": "Design theory" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-5", "content": [{ "text": "Communication theory" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s16-6", "content": [{ "text": "Human Computer Interaction theory (HCI), etc." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide17-h3-coupling",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Example: Theory of Coupling and Cohesion" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide17-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s17-1", "content": [{ "text": "Concepts: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "High cohesion (modules focused on one task), low coupling (minimal interdependencies)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s17-2", "content": [{ "text": "Laws: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "High cohesion + low coupling → maintainable, reusable code." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s17-3", "content": [{ "text": "Boundary: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Relevant for OOP and modular design; less critical in small scripts or prototypes." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide18-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Role of Theory in Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide18-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-1", "content": [{ "text": "Theory can be a goal or guide to research." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-2", "content": [{ "text": "The role of theory in research is to provide a frame of reference." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-3", "content": [{ "text": "Answers that result from research are formulated into theory." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-4", "content": [{ "text": "Theory is a tentative explanation for the facts and findings that evolve from the research process." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-5", "content": [{ "text": "Theory is used to guide and direct future research." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-6", "content": [{ "text": "Theories are developed based on what is observed or experienced, often times in the real world." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s18-7", "content": [{ "text": "Changed as we gather new facts and observe new relationship." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide19-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Concepts in Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide19-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Variables - any characteristic that varies (i.e., more than one value). Can be: Categorical or numerical, Discrete or continuous." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide19-h3",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Types of Variables in Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide19-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s19-1", "content": [{ "text": "Independent (IV)" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s19-2", "content": [{ "text": "Dependent (DV)" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Types of Reasoning" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Integration of Deduction and Induction forms the scientific method.", "bold": true }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-h3-ded",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Deductive Reasoning" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-p2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Deductive reasoning begins with general statements (premises) and, through logical argument, comes to a specific conclusion." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Often used for generating our hypotheses in research." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-p4",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "When we are using deductive reasoning, your conclusion will be correct if all the statements you say is correct." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-h4-ex",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "content": [{ "text": "Example:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide20-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s20-1", "content": [{ "text": "All students in this class play guitar" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s20-2", "content": [{ "text": "Selam is the student of this class" }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s20-3", "content": [{ "text": "Therefore, Selam plays guitar" }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-h3-ind",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Inductive Reasoning" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Inductive reasoning starts from specific observations then develops a general conclusion from them." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-p2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "General conclusions based on many specific observations." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "When using inductive reasoning, correct observations won't necessarily lead you to a correct general conclusion." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-h4-ex",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "content": [{ "text": "Example:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide21-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s21-1", "content": [{ "text": "Every quiz has been easy, therefore the test will be easy." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s21-2", "content": [{ "text": "The teacher used PPT in the last few classes, therefore the teacher will use PPT tomorrow." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide22-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Contribution and Originality" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide22-p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "1. Research Originality: ", "bold": true },
          { "text": "Novelty in ideas, methods, or perspectives that advance the field i.e. "},
          { "text": "What's new?", "italic": true },
          { "text": " (e.g., a first-of-its-kind approach)." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide22-p2-ex1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "Example: ", "bold": true },
          { "text": "First hybrid testing framework combining AI-based fuzzing with symbolic execution to uncover edge-case vulnerabilities." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide22-p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "2. Research Contribution: ", "bold": true },
          { "text": "Tangible impact on theory, practice, or tools in the field i.e. "},
          { "text": "Why does it matter?", "italic": true },
          { "text": " (e.g., measurable improvements, adoption, or paradigm shifts)." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide22-p4-ex2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "text": "Example: ", "bold": true },
          { "text": "Empirical validation showing a new DevOps pipeline optimization reduces deployment failures by 35% in industry case studies." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide23-h3",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Identify Contribution or Originality" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide23-q",
        "type": "alert",
        "style": "info",
        "title": [{ "text": "Activity: Justify your choice" }],
        "content": [
            { "text": "Identify which one is Contribution or Originality for the following points and justify your choice:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide23-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": true,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s23-1", "content": [{ "text": "Proposing a new algorithm for real-time data processing." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s23-2", "content": [{ "text": "Enhancing an existing tool (e.g., adding AI-based code suggestions to IDEs)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s23-3", "content": [{ "text": "Validating prior studies in new contexts (e.g., testing DevOps practices in African startups)." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide24-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Ethics in SE Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide24-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s24-1", "content": [{ "text": "Ethics ", "bold": true }, { "text": "is the study of moral principles that govern behavior, guiding what is considered \"right\" or \"wrong\" in a given context." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s24-2", "content": [{ "text": "It involves critical reflection on values, responsibilities, and the consequences of actions, ensuring fairness, respect, and accountability." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s24-3", "content": [{ "text": "Informed Consent: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Disclosing data usage in user studies (e.g., collecting GitHub commit histories)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s24-4", "content": [{ "text": "Privacy: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Anonymizing sensitive data (e.g., developer interviews)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s24-5", "content": [{ "text": "Bias Mitigation: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Avoiding skewed results in industry-sponsored studies." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide24-h3-act",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Activities:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide24-q",
        "type": "alert",
        "style": "info",
        "content": [{ "text": "\"What ethical issues might arise when collecting data from open-source GitHub repositories?\"" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide24-citation",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
            { "text": "Citation: ", "bold": true },
            { "text": "Mauthner (2002): \"Ethical research respects participant autonomy and confidentiality.\"", "italic": true }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide25-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Some Terminologies in Research" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c1-sm-block-slide25-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-1", "content": [{ "text": "Data: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Measurement of records of facts made under specific conditions." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-2", "content": [{ "text": "Hypothesis: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Tentative assumption of the study or expected results of the study." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-3", "content": [{ "text": "Independent variable: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "The part of the experiment that the researcher is manipulating; also called experimental or treatment variable." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-4", "content": [{ "text": "Dependent variable: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "The effect of the Independent variable." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-5", "content": [{ "text": "Population: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "A total number of subjects which they abide the inclusion and exclusion criteria." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-6", "content": [{ "text": "Review: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "A research paper that is a critical evaluation of research on a particular topic." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c1-sm-li-s25-7", "content": [{ "text": "Research proposal / Synopsis: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "A formal preparation that includes introduction, review of literature and proposed method of conducting study." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
